item.title: Syrian, Russian Airstrikes Target Rebels in Last Stronghold
item.description: Syrian and Russian airstrikes on the last rebel stronghold in Syria have intensified in recent days, raising fears of a military offensive that the U.N. has long warned would cause a humanitarian disaster.

item.title: U.K. Parliament Votes to Delay Brexit as Turmoil Drags On
item.description: British lawmakers are expected to vote to delay the U.K.’s departure from the European Union, scheduled for March 29, in the latest installment in an extraordinary week for the Brexit saga.

item.title: NATO Members Lift Military Spending, but Remain Below Goals
item.description: NATO members are nudging up military spending in response to Russian aggression and hectoring from President Trump, but remain far from their spending goals, according to an alliance report.

item.title: Want to Understand China's Latest Politics? Watch This Rap Video
item.description: At Beijing’s annual ‘Two Sessions’ confab, delegates examine policies page-by-page, and the Communist Party just needs to get citizens to pay heed; maybe a song about ‘cloned macaques’ will help.

item.title: Labor Lawyer Takes On Mexico's Exporters, Wins Higher Wages
item.description: Mexican labor lawyer Susana Prieto has become a driving force in a growing workers movement winning higher pay from the maquiladoras, the companies that assemble products for export to the U.S.

item.title: China Aims to Placate U.S. With Law Banning Theft of Trade Secrets
item.description: China made last-minute changes to a proposed foreign-investment law, trying to address U.S. complaints about forced technology transfer and bolster a compromise seen as crucial to striking a trade deal.
